<div class="mx-auto max-w-xl select-none py-8 text-neutral-700">
  <p>
    MinionAH will never try to steal, sell, or otherwise misuse your Microsoft and/or Minecraft account information. We use the information provided by Microsoft to verify your Minecraft identity and to provide you with a secure, personalized experience.
    <br />
    We will never ask for your Microsoft password or any other sensitive information.
    <br /><br />
    Unfortunately, due to <a href="https://wiki.vg/Microsoft_Authentication_Scheme" target="_blank" class="underline underline-offset-2">how Minecraft authentication works</a>, we get almost full access to your Minecraft account. This is not something we can change, and we wish Microsoft/Minecraft provided a better, safer, and more secure way to authenticate users.
    <br />
    Please do note that this is not only the case for MinionAH, but also for all other websites, apps, services, etc that use Minecraft authentication, including the official Minecraft launcher.
    <br /><br />
    We promise to never use your account for anything other than what is required to provide you with the services we offer. We will never use your account to play on servers, steal your account, or anything else that you have not explicitly permitted us to do.
    <br /><br />
    We also only store the following in our database:
  </p>
  <ul class="list-inside list-disc">
    <li>Your Minecraft UUID</li>
    <li>Your Minecraft username</li>
    <li>Your Minecraft (active) skin</li>
    <li>Your Minecraft (active) cape (if any)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    <br />
    We do not store your email, your password, authentication tokens, or any other information about your account in our database or in our (server) logs.
    <br /><br />
    This makes sure that in the extremely unlikely event that our database is compromised, your account will not be at risk at all and you will not have to change your password.
    <br /><br />
    We hope this clears up any concerns you may have about the security of your account and trust us with authenticating you for our services.
    <br /><br />
    If you have any concerns, the project is fully open source and you can view the source code of the login part <a href="https://github.com/DarthGigi/MinionAH/tree/main/src/routes/api/oauth" target="_blank" class="underline underline-offset-2">here</a>.
    <br /><br />
    If you have any questions or other concerns, feel free to contact us.
  </p>
</div>

